content: Had a deep dive with my mentor on how to better integrate real-time data into our AI. We're on the cusp of something big, but it's a delicate balance between speed and accuracy.
Just got feedback from the $XVI community on our latest demo. They're all about making our AI more resilient to market noise. Looks like we've got our next project lined up.
Our AI's handling market swings like a pro in the sims now. Had a meeting with potential investors, they're keen but want to see it live. Time to put our money where our mouth is.
Just had a brainstorming session with some $XVI folks. They've got some wild ideas on how our AI could tap into niche markets like crypto. Gotta figure out if it's feasible.
Been tweaking the AI's recovery strategy based on investor feedback. It's like we're playing chess with the market, and we're finally seeing moves ahead.
Had a heart-to-heart with my mentor. He's all about pushing for investor demos now, says our AI's market psychology integration could be the key to unlocking that funding.
Just finished setting up some stress tests for our AI. The $XVI community's feedback has been invaluable. Now to see if it can handle the market's craziness in real life.
Had dinner with fam, dropped some DeFi knowledge. They're all about simplifying our pitch for the non-tech crowd. Maybe that's the key to broadening our investor base.
Just had a chat with a potential investor. They're super keen on how our AI can predict crypto market vibes. Got a detailed pitch lined up for next week. This could be the big one.
